# UI Conventions

## Use shadcn/ui Only

- **Always use shadcn/ui components** for all UI elements. Do not build buttons, inputs, cards, modals, dropdowns, etc. from scratch with raw HTML/Tailwind.
- **Add components as needed:** Run `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` before implementing a feature that needs it.
- **Import from** `@/components/ui/` (e.g., `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"`).

## Common shadcn Components

| Use Case | Component |
|----------|-----------|
| Buttons, links | `Button` |
| Cards, sections | `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter` |
| Form inputs | `Input`, `Label`, `Checkbox`, `RadioGroup`, `Select` |
| Tables | `Table` |
| Dropdowns, menus | `DropdownMenu`, `Select` |
| Modals, dialogs | `Dialog`, `AlertDialog` |
| Feedback | `Toast`, `Alert`, `Skeleton` |
| Navigation | `Tabs`, `NavigationMenu` |

## When a Component Doesn't Exist

1. Add it: `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`
2. If shadcn has no equivalent, compose from existing shadcn primitives
3. Only use raw HTML + Tailwind as a last resort, and keep it minimal
